      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is showing me a BSOD (Blue Screen of Death) with stop code: WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR. They want me to:\n\n1. Investigate this using enterprise root cause analysis\n2. Tell them its fixability score using iFix\n3. Tell how reliable it is\n4. Whether they can spend time improving PC temperature5. All components are okay but they don't want to stress test them\n6. Want a decent assessment using PowerShell and Python tools\n\nFirst, let me understand the error:\n- WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is a Windows Hardware Error Architecture error\n- This typically indicates a hardware failure\n- Common causes:\n  - CPU overheating\n  - Faulty RAM\n  - PSU issues\n  - Overclocking instability\n  - Motherboard issues\n\nThe user wants me to use PowerShell and Python to check their system. I should:\n1. Check Windows Event Viewer logs for WHEA errors\n2. Check system temperatures\n3. Check RAM health\n4. Check disk health\n5. Look for other hardware-related errors\n\nSince this is a Windows system, I can use PowerShell commands to gather information. I cannot directly run PowerShell in this environment (I'm in a Linux environment based on the system prompt), but I can provide the user with commands they can run.\n\nHowever, the system prompt says I'm in a Windows environment (win32, powershell). Let me check what tools I have available. I have the bash tool which says it's for Windows PowerShell. So I should be able to run PowerShell commands.\n\nLet me investigate by:\n1. Checking event logs for WHEA errors\n2. Checking system temperatures\n3. Checking hardware information4. Looking for recent crashes\n\nLet me start by gathering system information and checking for WHEA errors.",
