    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now let me analyze the bugcheck codes and do some more investigation. Let me also look at the specific crash dump files and analyze the WHEA errors more carefully.\n\nKey findings so far:\n1. WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR from the BSOD photo\n2. Multiple BSOD crashes with different bugcheck codes:\n   - 0x0000012b (TDR_TIMEOUT_DETECTED or FAULTY_HARDWARE_CORRUPTED_PAGE) - appeared twice (June 20, May 12)\n   - 0x000000be (ATTEMPTED_WRITE_TO_READONLY_MEMORY) - appeared twice (June 17, May 15)\n3. Kernel-Power Event 41 (unexpected shutdowns) on July 3\n4. i5-7300HQ CPU (laptop, Kaby Lake)\n5. Mixed RAM: SK Hynix 8GB + Samsung 8GB (different manufacturers - potential compatibility issue)\n6. BIOS from 2021 - could be outdated\n7. Disks are healthy (HDD + NVMe SSD)\n8. GPU: Intel HD 630 + GTX 1050\n\nThe bugcheck codes are very telling:\n- 0x12b = FAULTY_HARDWARE_CORRUPTED_PAGE - This is a known WHEA-related error indicating uncorrectable hardware error\n- 0xbe = ATTEMPTED_WRITE_TO_READONLY_MEMORY - Memory corruption\n\nBoth point to memory issues. The mixed RAM modules (SK Hynix + Samsung) at 2400MHz on an i5-7300HQ could be problematic.\n\nLet me do more analysis.",
      "timestamp": 1783146359560
    },
